<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-03-26T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-03-26T13:00:00-05:00" n="56" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d56">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/1088: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-03-26T13:00:00-05:00">March 26, 1930—1
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>108. Your 219, March 25, 6p.m.</p>
                        <p>1. Suggestion in Legation’s 190, March 12, 11 a.m., paragraph 3, was
                            communicated to Catholic authorities, and you are confidentially
                            informed that the latter state they are taking measures toward complying
                            with the suggestion.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>